Introduction

   FreeGuide is an offline TV listings programme. It uses parser
   programmes to extract TV information from web pages and stores them
   for viewing without the need to connect to the Internet. The viewer
   allows the user to view television listings and create customised TV
   guides by selecting programmes and by building up a favourites list.
   For the moment, it only does UK listings, but it is designed to make
   it very easy to add other countries, especially the US and Canada as
   there are XMLTV scripts for these countries already written.

   FreeGuide is copyright ©2001 by Andy Balaam. Please do send ideas,
   bugs and comments to me at [9]freeguide@artificialworlds.net. I
   welcome contributions from others. FreeGuide's home page is at
   [10]http://freeguide-tv.sourceforge.net. You can contact me at the
   Centre for Computational Neuroscience and Robotics (CCNR), University
   of Sussex, Falmer, Brighton, UK.

   FreeGuide uses the XMLTV format and parsers developed by the very
   friendly people at XMLTV ([11]
   http://www.doc.ic.ac.uk/~epa98/work/apps/xmltv/ and
   [12]http://sourceforge.net/projects/xmltv). All the XMLTV code,
   READMEs and copyright notices may be found in the "xmltv" subdirectory
   of the freeguide programme directory.

   FreeGuide contains a little code by Slava Pestov from the Jedit
   project ([13]www.jedit.org).

   Referring to the crimson XML parser (crimson.jar): This product
   includes software developed by the Apache Software Foundation
   (http://www.apache.org/). See the file gui-java/crimsonlicence.txt for
   details.

